PN,31802
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1780862761
OL,3,CTaipei City Zoo receives a pair of red
OL,4,Cpandas from China
OL,6,FThe two pandas have yet to be named.
OL,7,FWhile the male panda immediately began
OL,8,Fto explore his new home and ate, the
OL,9,Ffemale remained cautious and preferred
OL,10,Fto observe, the Taipei Zoo said.
OL,12,FTaipei last received red pandas from a
OL,13,Fzoo in China's Fujian province in
OL,14,F2014, according to the Taipei Times.
OL,15,FThe animals are endemic to China, as
OL,16,Fwell as Nepal, Laos and Myanmar, among
OL,17,Fothers.
OL,19,FTaipei will send white-handed gibbons
OL,20,Fto Shanghai as part of the exchange,
OL,21,Fthe Taipei Times said.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/4
